  ;; ── GPIO Assignment table as schematic text ──────────────────────
  (text "ESP32-WROVER-E GPIO ASSIGNMENT\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nIO0   → BOOT button (pull-up R2 10k)          strapping\nIO2   → ENCODER_A  (pull-up 10k, 10nF debounce)\nIO4   → ENCODER_B  (pull-up 10k, 10nF debounce)\nIO5   → ENCODER_SW (pull-up 10k)\nIO12  → LCD_DC                                 strapping: keep low at boot\nIO13  → LCD_BL (PWM LEDC ch0)\nIO14  → LCD_RST\nIO15  → SPI_CLK  (VSPI SCLK)\nIO18  → I2S_BCLK\nIO19  → I2S_LRCK  (WS)\nIO21  → I2S_DIN   (data from ES7243E)\nIO22  → I2C_SCL   (SI4732 + ES7243E)\nIO23  → I2C_SDA   (SI4732 + ES7243E)\nIO25  → SPI_MOSI  (VSPI MOSI)\nIO26  → LCD_CS\nIO27  → SI_RESET  (active-low)\nIO32  → AUDIO_MUTE (SI4732 MUTE, active-high)\nIO33  → AMP_SD    (MAX98357A SD_MODE, active-high=play)\nIO34  → BT_LED    (open-drain output)\nEN    → RESET via R1 10k pull-up + SW1\nTXD0  → CP2102N RXD\nRXD0  → CP2102N TXD\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nNote: IO34-39 are input-only on WROVER-E\nNote: Bluetooth Classic uses internal antenna (IPEX optional)\nNote: PSRAM uses IO16/IO17 internally - do NOT route externally"
    (at 220 100)
    (effects (font (size 1.7 1.7)) (justify left))
  )
)
